Sensing there might be little experience here with how protests work at slaughterhouses, trucks arrive and approach gates, usually having to wait depending upon how many are arriving at a given time. Protests happen during this waiting time/ near the gate. Often, it is a time to bear witness to the animals bc the time to stop the process has passed. The animals are stamping, standing in inches of urine and feces, and very afraid. They haven‚Äôt had water or rest sometimes for days. There would be no urgency for a truck driver at this point to plow through the entry area like this. We recognize that this work of transportation and slaughter itself is not work of choice, highly stressful with high turnover.

Assumption (see above)on the part of people who don‚Äôt have/don‚Äôt understand mental illness (it is an illness): ‚Äúnot having the balls to get help‚Äù. 
Getting help, even with good insurance, is a marathon; or rather like back to back marathons. The mental health system and its processes - a literal labyrinth- takes years to navigate. That, in itself, can be a cause - or the proverbial straw- that leads to suicide. 
Some illnesses are themselves barriers to getting help by definition and nature of their symptoms. 
A large part of success around this will be getting the general public psycho educated.
